HEADWORD: Wanty
<hw>Wan"ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[For <ets>womb
tie</ets>, that is, belly<?/and. See <er>Womb</er>, and
<er>Tie</er>.]</ety> <def>A surcingle, or strap of leather, used for
binding a load upon the back of a beast; also, a leather tie; a short
wagon rope.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

